# Active quest pointer

Top-level pointer for the millwright-overseer-development-machine quest folder. Records which per-cycle subfolder under `quest/` is currently active.

Each `/mo-run` creates a new subfolder named `quest/<slug>/` and writes the four cycle files (`todo-list.md`, `summary.md`, `progress.md`, `queue-rationale.md`) inside it. Historical subfolders are preserved across cycles so PMs can query past task lists, summaries, and queue rationales as a permanent record.

This file is the single mutable piece of top-level state under `quest/`:

- **`slug`** — points at the active subfolder (`quest/<slug>/`). Null when no cycle is active.
- **`status`** — `active` while a cycle is in flight, `archived` once it ends, `none` immediately after `/mo-init` (no cycle has ever started).
- **`journal-folders`** — the list `/mo-run` was invoked with; preserved on `archived`/`none` for context.

Path-resolution helpers (`scripts/internal/common.sh`) read this file to map `quest/todo-list.md` references to `quest/<slug>/todo-list.md` for the active cycle. Do not hand-edit; use `scripts/quest.sh` to manage the lifecycle.
